      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC4e2204382b2310058d68a5fdf30dcfc4"></a>Refitting the fuel tank flange
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4580"> </a>Duly grease the sealing washer (3), position the flange, and refit by reversing the steps of the removal procedure.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4582"> </a>Orientate fuel pump (2) with the arrows on plate (M) facing the front part of tank (8).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4584"> </a>Tighten the six nuts (1) to a torque of 6 Nm ±10%.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_8_001803651.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4589"> </a>Apply specified grease on seal (C) of fuel sensor (7).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4591"> </a>Insert fuel sensor (7) in tank (8) and orientate it so that tabs (D) and (E) match with recesses (F) and (G) on tank entry
            (H).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4593"> </a>To fix the sensor position and tighten ring-nut (L) to 8 Nm ±10%.
         </div>
      </div>
